India's state-owned National ThermalPower Corp said it has signed an agreement to borrow 169.1 mlnmarks at a fixed annual 6.48 pct interest for 15 years andeight months, an NTPC official said.    The agreement signed last Saturday in Hong Kong with asyndicate of eight Indian and foreign banks including StateBank of India (London), Bankers Trust Co (Hong Kong) andGrindlays Bank Plc (London) fixes the draw-down period at 68months, the official said.    Repayments are in 20 half-yearly instalments starting fromthe 68th month. REUTER&#3;